From: mt7902-debian-trixie contributors
Subject: [PATCH] btmtk: recognize MT7902 hardware variant

The btmtk USB setup path matches the chip ID reported by the device
against a switch/case list in btmtk_usb_setup. On kernels that predate
upstream commit "Bluetooth: btmtk: Add support for MT7902"
(merged after the 6.12.x stable cycle), MT7902 (dev_id 0x7902) falls
into the default branch and the driver bails out with:

    Bluetooth: hciN: Unsupported hardware variant (00007902)

This patch backports the minimal additions needed to bring the chip up
on the existing 79xx code path, which already covers MT7921/7922/7925
/7961: the firmware filename define and a `case 0x7902:` entry in the
variant switch. No changes to btmtk_setup_firmware_79xx() or
btmtk_fw_get_filename() are required, since both already handle the
0x79xx-style dev_ids generically and the firmware file MediaTek ships
for MT7902 follows the same naming convention
(BT_RAM_CODE_MT%04x_1_%x_hdr.bin).

Tested on Debian trixie kernel 6.12.73+deb13-amd64 with USB 0e8d:7902.

--- a/btmtk.h
+++ b/btmtk.h
@@ -5,6 +5,7 @@
 #define FIRMWARE_MT7663		"mediatek/mt7663pr2h.bin"
 #define FIRMWARE_MT7668		"mediatek/mt7668pr2h.bin"
 #define FIRMWARE_MT7922		"mediatek/BT_RAM_CODE_MT7922_1_1_hdr.bin"
+#define FIRMWARE_MT7902		"mediatek/BT_RAM_CODE_MT7902_1_1_hdr.bin"
 #define FIRMWARE_MT7961		"mediatek/BT_RAM_CODE_MT7961_1_2_hdr.bin"
 #define FIRMWARE_MT7925		"mediatek/mt7925/BT_RAM_CODE_MT7925_1_1_hdr.bin"

--- a/btmtk.c
+++ b/btmtk.c
@@ -1326,6 +1326,7 @@
 	case 0x7922:
 	case 0x7925:
 	case 0x7961:
+	case 0x7902:
 		btmtk_fw_get_filename(fw_bin_name, sizeof(fw_bin_name), dev_id,
 				      fw_version, fw_flavor);

@@ -1495,5 +1496,6 @@
 MODULE_FIRMWARE(FIRMWARE_MT7663);
 MODULE_FIRMWARE(FIRMWARE_MT7668);
 MODULE_FIRMWARE(FIRMWARE_MT7922);
+MODULE_FIRMWARE(FIRMWARE_MT7902);
 MODULE_FIRMWARE(FIRMWARE_MT7961);
 MODULE_FIRMWARE(FIRMWARE_MT7925);
